Introduction

Orange Caramel is a South Korean female sub-group of After School formed by Pledis Entertainment in June 2010. The unit debuted in 2010 with the single "Magic Girl" from their mini-album 'The First Mini Album' becoming a commercial success for its famous choreography and concept.

The unit sought success in 2014 during the release of their third single "Catallena" on March 12, becoming a major hit in South Korea, widely known for members screaming during the introduction. Orange Caramel later released their fourth single, "My Copycat" where viewers could spot differences in side-by-side shots.
